OL,3,CEmergency services failings found over
OL,4,Cdeath of student
OL,6,FOne was dismissed from the PSNI, the
OL,7,Fother was given a written warning. The
OL,8,Fdismissal was set aside on appeal, but
OL,9,Fthe officer died before a new hearing
OL,10,Fcould be held.
OL,12,FA third officer was disciplined for
OL,13,Ffailing to submit and retain her own
OL,14,Foriginal signed statement about the
OL,15,Fincident, while another officer who
OL,16,Famended the statement and failed to
OL,17,Fensure that the original was kept, was
OL,18,Fgiven advice to improve her conduct.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}           G13/19
