OL,3,CEmergency services failings found over
OL,4,Cdeath of student
OL,6,F"Frontline staff must recognise their
OL,7,Fcollective professional duty of care,
OL,8,Fand they should be supported in their
OL,9,Fresponsibilities by agreed inter-
OL,10,Fagency professional practice."
OL,12,FResponding to the findings, Assistant
OL,13,FChief Constable Anthony McNally said:
OL,14,F"Our thoughts today are very much with
OL,15,Feveryone who has been affected by this
OL,16,Fawful and tragic incident.
OL,18,F"We recognise that this will again be
OL,19,Fa particularly difficult day for
OL,20,FShannon McQuillan's family, Owen and
OL,21,Fhis family.
OL,26,@nD@AOUrD@^O]vD@AOUzD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}           G17/19
